::{{DIcon|Talk}} You mentioned your faith in Cerces...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504003103-->
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Yeah! My family has upheld faith in Cerces for generations, upholding the dissemination of knowledge as a sacred duty, and this librarium is a legacy from our ancestors. My brother is a super duper erudite scholar who read so much that he already earned his place as a Garden of Life scholar.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' My brother, the great scholar, thinks my made-up stories about underdogs and reincarnation are indecency. If he found them out, he'd probably say that they don't match Cerces' notion of rationality and could provoke the Titans.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' So, I have to juggle running the store during the day and writing novels in secret at night.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are followers of Cerces so conservative?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why not just give up your faith in Cerces?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504003108-->
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Hey, don't blame Cerces. All my overflowing inspirations actually come from the Bough of Rift, which can see into the past and future.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Blame my brother. You old stiff, Theophis! Cerces has lived over 800 brilliant divine lives through my pen! Isn't that more exciting than being a dull Titan on your altar!?
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} How can I buy the books you've written?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504003111-->
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Shh... Keep your voice down. You never know who might be listening.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' I stash them away in a secret compartment in the back room to keep them safe from my brother's prying eyes. If you're interested, I can fetch you a couple.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Speaking of that, there's a new challenge for me. Nowadays, customers prefer lighter fiction. Quick-paced plots, humorous tales, and mini comedy tablets featuring 30-second stories are flying off the shelves.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' With more authors joining in, I'm running out of space to store their books in my secret compartment. I need to find a solution...
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why don't you talk about it with your brother?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504003116-->
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Even though I complain about his outdated views, deep down I don't really want him to change.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Our parents died in the black tide disaster long ago. He was just a six-year-old child back then, but he had to provide for both of us. As time passed, he worked on rebuilding our family librarium, while also doing the best he could to nurture me intellectually.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' Even though I'm an adult now, he still feels responsible for me... It's just that the line between care and overprotection is a bit blurry, hehe.
:::'''Ctesiphona:''' I don't blame him. I'd rather work harder on my own if keeping everything a secret makes life easier for him.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I don't have any other questions.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504003121-->
